[{"location":"api/values.html#Integer-Order-Characteristic-Values-1","page":"Integer Order Characteristic Values","title":"Integer Order Characteristic Values","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/values.html#","page":"Integer Order Characteristic Values","title":"Integer Order Characteristic Values","text":"Modules = [Mathieu]\nPages   = [\"integerorder_evals.jl\"]\nOrder   = [:function]\nPrivate = true","category":"page"},{"location":"api/values.html#Mathieu.a","page":"Integer Order Characteristic Values","title":"Mathieu.a","text":"a(m,q)\n\nCompute the characteristic value a_m(q) corresponding to an even (cosine-elliptic) solution to the angular Mathieu equation. m is the order of the solution and must be an integer m=0123.\n\nPass a vector, e.g. m=0:4, to compute multiple characteristic values efficiently.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/values.html#Mathieu.aa","page":"Integer Order Characteristic Values","title":"Mathieu.aa","text":"aa(n,q)\n\nCompute the characteristic value a_2n+1(q) corresponding to an even (cosine-elliptic), π-antiperiodic (2π-periodic) solution to the angular Mathieu equation, for n=0123.\n\nPass a vector, e.g. n=0:4, to compute multiple characteristic values efficiently.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/values.html#Mathieu.ap","page":"Integer Order Characteristic Values","title":"Mathieu.ap","text":"ap(n,q)\n\nCompute the characteristic value a_2n(q) corresponding to an even (cosine-elliptic), π-periodic solution to the angular Mathieu equation, for n=0123.\n\nPass a vector, e.g. n=0:4, to compute multiple characteristic values efficiently.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/values.html#Mathieu.b","page":"Integer Order Characteristic Values","title":"Mathieu.b","text":"b(m,q)\n\nCompute the characteristic value b_m(q) corresponding to an odd (sine-elliptic) solution to the angular Mathieu equation. m is the order of the solution and must be an integer, excluding 0, m=1234.\n\nPass a vector, e.g. m=1:5, to compute multiple characteristic values efficiently.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/values.html#Mathieu.ba","page":"Integer Order Characteristic Values","title":"Mathieu.ba","text":"ba(n,q)\n\nCompute the characteristic value b_2n+1(q) corresponding to an odd (sine-elliptic), π-antiperiodic (2π-periodic) solution to the angular Mathieu equation, for n=0123.\n\nPass a vector, e.g. n=0:4, to compute multiple characteristic values efficiently.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/values.html#Mathieu.bp","page":"Integer Order Characteristic Values","title":"Mathieu.bp","text":"bp(n,q)\n\nCompute the characteristic value b_2n+2(q) corresponding to an odd (sine-elliptic), π-periodic solution to the angular Mathieu equation, for n=0123.\n\nPass a vector, e.g. n=0:4, to compute multiple characteristic values efficiently.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/values.html#Mathieu.char_aper","page":"Integer Order Characteristic Values","title":"Mathieu.char_aper","text":"char_aper(m,q)\n\nCompute the characteristic value a_m+1(q) for even m, or b_m(q) for odd m. These characteristic values correspond respectively to even and odd π-antiperiodic (2π-periodic) solutions to the angular Mathieu equation, for n=0123.\n\nm value\n0 a_1\n1 b_1\n2 a_3\n3 b_3\n4 a_5\n⋮ ⋮\n\nPass a vector, e.g. m=0:4, to compute multiple characteristic values efficiently.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/values.html#Mathieu.char_per","page":"Integer Order Characteristic Values","title":"Mathieu.char_per","text":"char_per(m,q)\n\nCompute the characteristic value a_m(q) for even m, or b_m+1(q) for odd m. These characteristic values correspond respectively to even and odd π-periodic solutions to the angular Mathieu equation, for n=0123.\n\nm value\n0 a_0\n1 b_2\n2 a_2\n3 b_4\n4 a_4\n⋮ ⋮\n\nPass a vector, e.g. m=0:4, to compute multiple characteristic values efficiently.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_surf.html#","page":"Mathieu Surface Plots","title":"Mathieu Surface Plots","text":"using Mathieu, PyPlot\nisdir(\"img\") || mkdir(\"img\")\ninclude(joinpath(@__DIR__,\"..\",\"..\",\"..\",\"examples\",\"surfaceplots.jl\"))\nsavefig(joinpath(\"img\",\"surf_5.svg\"),transparent=true); close()\nsavefig(joinpath(\"img\",\"surf_4.svg\"),transparent=true); close()\nsavefig(joinpath(\"img\",\"surf_3.svg\"),transparent=true); close()\nsavefig(joinpath(\"img\",\"surf_2.svg\"),transparent=true); close()\nsavefig(joinpath(\"img\",\"surf_1.svg\"),transparent=true); close()","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_surf.html#Mathieu-Surface-Plots-1","page":"Mathieu Surface Plots","title":"Mathieu Surface Plots","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_surf.html#","page":"Mathieu Surface Plots","title":"Mathieu Surface Plots","text":"We plot Mathieu functions for q  between 0 and 10 in order to show the periodic and anti-periodic properties of the sine-elliptic and cosine-elliptic solutions.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_surf.html#","page":"Mathieu Surface Plots","title":"Mathieu Surface Plots","text":"The plots were inspired by the NIST Digital Library of Mathematical Functions.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_surf.html#","page":"Mathieu Surface Plots","title":"Mathieu Surface Plots","text":"(Image: surf_1) (Image: surf_2) (Image: surf_3) (Image: surf_4) (Image: surf_5)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_surf.html#","page":"Mathieu Surface Plots","title":"Mathieu Surface Plots","text":"The code used to generate these plots is also available in the example folder of the package.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_surf.html#","page":"Mathieu Surface Plots","title":"Mathieu Surface Plots","text":"using Markdown: parse\nparse(\"\"\"\n```julia\n$(read(joinpath(@__DIR__,\"..\",\"..\",\"..\",\"examples\",\"surfaceplots.jl\"),String))\n```\n\"\"\")","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_funs.html#","page":"Mathieu Function Plots","title":"Mathieu Function Plots","text":"using Mathieu, PyPlot\n!isdir(\"img\") && mkdir(\"img\")\ninclude(joinpath(@__DIR__,\"..\",\"..\",\"..\",\"examples\",\"functionplots.jl\"))\nsavefig(joinpath(\"img\",\"funs_10.svg\"),transparent=true); close()\nsavefig(joinpath(\"img\",\"funs_1.svg\"),transparent=true); close()","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_funs.html#Mathieu-Function-Plots-1","page":"Mathieu Function Plots","title":"Mathieu Function Plots","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_funs.html#","page":"Mathieu Function Plots","title":"Mathieu Function Plots","text":"We plot Mathieu functions for q = 1 and 10 in order to show the periodic and anti-periodic properties of the sine-elliptic and cosine-elliptic solutions.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_funs.html#","page":"Mathieu Function Plots","title":"Mathieu Function Plots","text":"The plots were inspired by the NIST Digital Library of Mathematical Functions.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_funs.html#","page":"Mathieu Function Plots","title":"Mathieu Function Plots","text":"(Image: function_1)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_funs.html#","page":"Mathieu Function Plots","title":"Mathieu Function Plots","text":"(Image: function_10)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_funs.html#","page":"Mathieu Function Plots","title":"Mathieu Function Plots","text":"The code used to generate these plots is also available in the example folder of the package.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/mathieu_funs.html#","page":"Mathieu Function Plots","title":"Mathieu Function Plots","text":"using Markdown: parse\nparse(\"\"\"\n```julia\n$(read(joinpath(@__DIR__,\"..\",\"..\",\"..\",\"examples\",\"functionplots.jl\"),String))\n```\n\"\"\")","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Mathieu.jl-1","page":"Home","title":"Mathieu.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"A package for computing integer order Mathieu functions and characteristic values.","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The notation used here mirrors the one in NIST's Digital Library of Mathematical Functions.","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The methods used to compute the functions and characteristic values are based on matrix diagonalization, and are explained in more details in Cojocaru 2008.","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: surf_5)","category":"page"},{"location":"api/functions.html#Integer-Order-Functions-1","page":"Integer Order Functions","title":"Integer Order Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/functions.html#","page":"Integer Order Functions","title":"Integer Order Functions","text":"Modules = [Mathieu]\nPages   = [\"integerorder_funs.jl\"]\nOrder   = [:function]\nPrivate = true","category":"page"},{"location":"api/functions.html#Mathieu.ce","page":"Integer Order Functions","title":"Mathieu.ce","text":"ce(m,q,z)\n\nCompute the cosine-elliptic Mathieu function textce_m(qz). m is the order of the solution and must be an integer m=0123.\n\nPass a vector, e.g. m=0:4 and/or z=LinRange(0,π,101), to compute the function for multiple orders and variables efficiently.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/functions.html#Mathieu.se","page":"Integer Order Functions","title":"Mathieu.se","text":"se(m,q,z)\n\nCompute the sine-elliptic Mathieu function textse_m(qz). m is the order of the solution and must be an integer, excluding 0, m=1234.\n\nPass a vector, e.g. m=1:5 and/or z=LinRange(0,π,101), to compute the function for multiple orders and variables efficiently.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"}]
